track_notes:
This route avoids any steep ascents.
First, take the WHR train to Rhyd Ddu station! Follow the track to Bwlch y Llan and cross the stile to take a public right of way SSW. Eventually there is a fence, which you can follow to the ridge line, to approach the summit from the SW. Actually you will find they are just sheep tracks. It is probably easier heading up-slope sooner. I passed to the NE of the copper workings.
Good parking at start of walk, nice views and a generally easy walk. Option to continue onto Snowdon and Y Lliwedd before returning via Watkin Path..

Total time (including ops): 3hr 30m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T3. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
track_title: Yr Aran Circuit from Rhyd Ddu. Jul 2019.
